methods.getReferenceQueue:
Get the reference queue for this cleaner.
 On the first call after construction or resetForUnitTests(), this method initializes the instance as
 a side effect. Initialization entails:
 
* Constructing a ReferenceQueue.
* Starting a daemon thread that will drain the reference queue and invoke
 CleanupReference.cleanup() on any CleanupReference dequeued.


Note: Java generics information - <RT>

:return: (java.lang.ref.ReferenceQueue<RT>) The ReferenceQueue constructed in the most recent initialization of this CleanupReferenceProcessor
 instance
methods.resetForUnitTests:
Reset this instance so that the next call to getReferenceQueue() will re-initialize it and provide a new
 queue.
 Results in eventual termination of the daemon thread that may have been draining the existing queue.

Note: Java generics information - io.deephaven.util.annotations.@TestUseOnly

text: Utility for draining a reference queue of CleanupReferences and invoking their cleanup methods.
